reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Coffee Station
reviews.reviewText: I am very please with this purchase. The instructions were easy to follow; the hardware and finish were of good quality. It took about 3 1/2 hours to assemble. The instructions do have door adjustments.The Sideboard Cabinet is very sturdy and looks amazing. I strongly recommend its purchase.We are using it as a coffee station and it serves that purpose superbly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Very impressed with the value for the money. After having to step back by the sheer number of pieces, the instructions were awesome and I had no problem with the assembly. Fully built, it looks great and feels very solid. I had a bit of concern about gaps in the doors, but reached out to the seller and got a quick and easy response that allowed me to adjust them. Definitely would recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love the look & storage this buffet has. I wish I knew how to adjust the doors to close the gap. Seems to be sturdy, and not the hardest thing to build, but came with so many parts. Took 3 1/2 hours to finish it. I would buy again.

reviews.reviewText: I ordered this with only one review to go off of. I was pleasantly surprised with the quality of this piece. It is very sturdy and looks very nice. Easy to assemble and arrived quickly. My only complaint is about half of the hinges were bent in a couple different places, however I was able to get them bent back enough to where they still work. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wow! Very Impressed.
reviews.reviewText: For a piece of furniture that needs to be assembled, this is about as good as it gets. The packaging and instructions were very well thought out. I loved that the parts were divided into their own individually lettered bag. Each letter was displayed on the instruction booklet which made it easy to understand exactly which part goes where. A philips screwdriver was included as well as an extra bag of spare parts (just in case!). Personally, I chose to use a cordless screwdriver but for those who don't own one, the included philips would be very helpful. The boards pre-drilled holes matched up perfectly with each other. I'm very impressed by the amount of thought, consideration and planning that went into this piece. I whole heartedly recommend this sideboard.
